WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.742
CHLOE:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.920 --> 00:07.083
CLARK: I wear the symbol to remind me
that I have a different destiny.

00:07.257 --> 00:11.000
TESS: I have waited so long for you
to admit your true Kryptonian heritage.

00:11.553 --> 00:13.635
My Earth father warned me
not to play God.

00:13.805 --> 00:16.638
But I tempted fate,
and because of that, he died.

00:16.808 --> 00:18.469
When you saw my fate,
what did you see?

00:18.643 --> 00:20.929
DR. FATE: Although Lex Luthor
is your ultimate opponent...

00:21.104 --> 00:22.264
...you will triumph over him.

00:23.773 --> 00:25.764
You walk the same path I do,
Chloe Sullivan.

00:25.942 --> 00:28.183
CHLOE:
Watchtower is ofﬁcially online.

00:28.361 --> 00:30.022
OLIVER:
You saved my life, Chloe.

00:30.196 --> 00:31.982
Both the myth and the man.

00:32.282 --> 00:33.863
What do you say, kid? Africa.

00:34.034 --> 00:36.901
Perry White offered me a job
at the foreign desk in Kenya.

00:37.078 --> 00:39.865
CLARK: Well, what would make you stay?
-I would stay for you.

00:40.040 --> 00:43.157
I think you leaving Metropolis
is the best thing for you right now.

00:44.002 --> 00:47.039
TESS:
You are the only one that can save us.

00:47.213 --> 00:48.589
The war has already begun.

00:50.550 --> 00:53.292
CHLOE: But what if every trial
has just been a preparation...

00:53.470 --> 00:55.506
...for you to make
the ultimate sacriﬁce?

00:56.890 --> 00:59.302
CARTER:
You have the capacity to break the chains...

00:59.476 --> 01:00.932
...that are holding you down, Clark.

01:02.103 --> 01:04.059
You will soar higher
than any one of us.

01:11.529 --> 01:14.441
-C|ark.
-Ollie, you need to get out of there now.

01:14.616 --> 01:15.731
CHLOE: Ollie!
OLIVER: Chloe!

01:15.909 --> 01:17.399
They're not Kandorian.

01:29.214 --> 01:32.001
CLARK: And now,
the ﬁnal season of Smallville.

01:35.720 --> 01:37.836
[PANTING]

01:43.019 --> 01:46.136
Clark! Clark. No.

01:46.731 --> 01:47.846
Clark?

01:49.567 --> 01:51.068
No.

01:55.031 --> 01:56.020
[SOBBING]

01:56.199 --> 01:57.359
Clark.

01:57.534 --> 01:59.195
Please.

01:59.869 --> 02:02.076
Please come back to me.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.800
[CROWS CAWING]

03:16.779 --> 03:18.064
[THUNDER CRASHES]

03:32.045 --> 03:33.125
JOR—EL:
KaI-EI.

03:36.883 --> 03:38.544
Jor-El.

03:45.350 --> 03:46.430
Am I dead?

03:46.601 --> 03:50.469
JOR-EL: You're teetering on the abyss
between life and death...

03:50.647 --> 03:53.559
...which is why I am still able
to reach you.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.689
My father’s grave.

03:57.612 --> 03:59.819
Why show me this?

04:01.324 --> 04:07.069
JOR-EL: After you die, this stone will be
all that is left of you in the world.

04:07.705 --> 04:09.570
I died to save the world.

04:09.749 --> 04:11.455
JOR-EL:
Evil never ends.

04:11.626 --> 04:14.117
By sacriﬁcing yourself...

04:14.295 --> 04:17.583
.y.ou've left the humans vulnerable
to future threats.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.043
I left a team of heroes behind
to protect them.

04:20.218 --> 04:23.710
JOR-EL: You were meant to be
Earth '8 greatest protector:

04:23.888 --> 04:29.383
Now they're about to face
the greatest evil without you.

04:32.146 --> 04:34.182
Then send me back.

04:34.941 --> 04:37.023
I know my fate.

04:37.944 --> 04:41.653
To step into the light.
To be a symbol of hope for them.

04:41.823 --> 04:47.068
JOR-EL: I told you to rule with strength,
but you chose the martst path.

04:47.245 --> 04:50.282
What makes you think
you deserve a second chance?

04:50.456 --> 04:53.414
I can do it. I can be their hero.

05:02.552 --> 05:04.292
Jor-El?

05:08.474 --> 05:11.807
Let me ﬁght this evil
like I always have.

05:13.855 --> 05:16.096
Send me back!

05:19.152 --> 05:21.063
[RUSTLING]

05:40.590 --> 05:41.579
Lex.

05:49.098 --> 05:51.760
Oh, God, Clark.

05:53.478 --> 05:55.093
Clark.

06:03.237 --> 06:04.272
Clark.

06:06.240 --> 06:07.855
Clark. Clark. Clark.

06:08.034 --> 06:09.444
[CLARK MOANS]

06:16.459 --> 06:17.915
Okay.

08:04.609 --> 08:06.565
[BANGING]

08:07.820 --> 08:09.606
Chloe, they're not Kandorian.

08:11.491 --> 08:12.606
[love you.

08:14.076 --> 08:15.452
[OLIVER GRUNTS]

08:19.790 --> 08:22.281
We 're coming for all of you.

08:43.439 --> 08:46.772
-Clark? You survived. How did you—?
-I didn't.

08:48.027 --> 08:49.983
Zod stabbed me with Blue Kryptonite.

08:50.154 --> 08:52.531
It kept us from ascending.

08:53.449 --> 08:56.236
I took the knife from him
and sent him away.

08:56.994 --> 09:01.033
And I guess I kind of— Kind of died.

09:02.291 --> 09:05.328
But I'm here now. And what about
the others? Did they make it?

09:05.753 --> 09:08.620
They're ﬁne. Can we go back
to the part where you died?

09:09.632 --> 09:11.497
It was more
of a near-death experience.

09:13.302 --> 09:16.465
Jor-El told me
that greater evil was coming.

09:17.890 --> 09:19.391
He sent me back to ﬁght it.

09:19.559 --> 09:22.892
Okay, I'm all for second chances,
but did he happen to give a name?

09:23.062 --> 09:25.553
No, but, Chloe,
before I left, I saw Lex.

09:28.568 --> 09:30.900
Dr. Fate said
he would be my ultimate opponent.

09:34.407 --> 09:38.150
Coming back to life,
not exactly covered by an HMO.

09:38.327 --> 09:41.034
Maybe he went off the grid,
to one of his own facilities.

09:41.205 --> 09:43.070
I kept a close eye on Luthor ﬂare-ups.

09:43.291 --> 09:48.035
I mean, Level 3,
Metro Pharmaceuticals, 33.1.

09:48.212 --> 09:49.998
Clark, all these projects are dead.

09:50.172 --> 09:52.504
Maybe he revived something
from years ago.

09:53.217 --> 09:55.879
Way back when there wasn't much
digital record to track.

09:56.053 --> 09:58.169
You know, if they did a story
at the Daily Planet...

09:58.347 --> 10:01.009
...they would have a hard copy
stored in the archives.

10:01.183 --> 10:04.550
I didn't get rid of Zod
just to let some other evil take his place.

10:12.528 --> 10:14.189
LOIS:
Lana.

10:15.031 --> 10:16.771
Pete.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.366
Chloe.

10:25.583 --> 10:28.700
And Mr. and Mrs. K
were always so overprotective.

10:28.878 --> 10:31.210
I'm the last one to know.

10:34.508 --> 10:35.759
[WHOOSH]

10:38.721 --> 10:40.257
Lois.

10:42.892 --> 10:47.056
-I thought you'd be in Africa by now.
-I postponed my trip.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.387
Maybe indeﬁnitely.

10:53.778 --> 10:56.064
This wouldn't have anything to do
with the Blur, would it?

10:57.114 --> 10:58.399
Well, kind of.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.077
Turns out he needs me after all.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.992
Really? Well, what makes you
say that?

11:11.921 --> 11:13.411
Well, I'll tell you, Clark.

11:14.799 --> 11:18.633
He just wrapped me up
in his muscular arms...

11:18.803 --> 11:25.265
...pulled me close and landed
the most passionate kiss on my lips.

11:25.976 --> 11:30.436
I can't lie to you, it was great.

11:35.611 --> 11:37.147
That was bold.

11:37.321 --> 11:40.028
Grabbing women from the shadows,
lip-smacking them...

11:40.199 --> 11:42.190
...and then running off into the night?

11:42.410 --> 11:46.699
Kind of makes you wonder what other
twisted fetishes he has in his tool box.

11:48.124 --> 11:50.456
So, Clark,
did you come here for a reason?

11:50.626 --> 11:52.662
Pressing story, maybe?

11:53.170 --> 11:55.661
Actual-- Yeah, I'm on
a really tight, uh, deadline.

12:00.636 --> 12:05.130
Whoops. Would you look at that? I dropped
my pen. I'm just gonna look for it.

12:08.978 --> 12:10.058
[CHUCKLES]

12:10.229 --> 12:14.563
Normally, I wouldn't deal with these dust
bunnies, but it's kind of my favorite pen.

12:16.652 --> 12:18.859
Not seeing it.

12:20.489 --> 12:21.649
Where are you, pen?

12:25.494 --> 12:27.155
Found it.

12:29.582 --> 12:32.244
Lucky for me,
it was right here on top of these ﬁles, so....

12:32.418 --> 12:33.908
Hmm.

12:36.338 --> 12:37.669
I'll go.

12:38.507 --> 12:39.587
Wait, Clark.

12:41.844 --> 12:43.209
Yeah, Lois? What is it?

12:44.597 --> 12:45.882
We need to talk.

12:48.225 --> 12:52.594
Well, I get now is not the time.
There's so much that I wanna tell you.

12:53.522 --> 12:54.853
Barn? Later?

12:56.108 --> 12:57.769
I'll be there.

13:01.864 --> 13:05.527
Chloe, I found a research facility linked
to LuthorCorp that wasn't in your ﬁles.

13:05.701 --> 13:08.192
Cadmus Labs.
Think you can dig up an address for me?

13:08.370 --> 13:12.989
Sorry, Clark, I would, but I'm not exactly
at Watchtower right now.

13:13.167 --> 13:15.032
[VOICES WHISPERING]

13:15.503 --> 13:18.461
VOICE:
She '8 here. Foolish girl.

13:18.631 --> 13:20.041
Who was that?

13:20.216 --> 13:21.547
VOICE:
But not chosen.

13:21.717 --> 13:24.208
Love is dangerous. Nabu knows.

13:25.554 --> 13:27.055
Chloe, where are you?

13:27.223 --> 13:31.216
Sorry, Clark,
but I knew you'd only try and stop me.

13:45.157 --> 13:47.239
[WHISPERING INTENSIFIES]

13:53.833 --> 13:55.573
Show me where Oliver is.

13:55.751 --> 14:00.120
VOICE: Would you sacriﬁce your sanity
to save the archer?

14:11.433 --> 14:13.298
[WHOOSH]

14:19.650 --> 14:21.390
Chloe.

14:23.279 --> 14:25.019
[GRUNTING]

14:31.453 --> 14:33.068
OLIVER:
I think this whole thing...

14:33.247 --> 14:36.660
...would be a lot more painful for me
if I could see your ugly face.

14:36.876 --> 14:40.494
What do you say we ditch this little
blindfold here and go full monty, huh?

14:40.671 --> 14:46.462
-You up for that?
-Well, it only seems fair you not see me.

14:47.970 --> 14:50.006
The world sat blind...

14:50.180 --> 14:53.798
...while cryptic symbols were carved
into its greatest monuments...

14:53.976 --> 14:57.139
...because all Earth's satellites
were either shut down or destroyed.

14:57.313 --> 15:01.932
All but one, yours.

15:03.193 --> 15:06.185
Well, I can explain that.

15:06.405 --> 15:09.317
See, I always buy quality
over quantity.

15:09.491 --> 15:11.322
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

15:12.995 --> 15:14.986
Your satellite was tracking them.

15:15.164 --> 15:19.874
Symbols that looked just like the Blur's,
which makes him a person of interest.

15:20.044 --> 15:22.330
But what's your connection to all this?

15:22.504 --> 15:24.495
[PANTING]
I told you.

15:24.798 --> 15:27.460
You got this whole thing wrong, okay?

15:27.635 --> 15:32.129
I'm what you call a good guy here!

15:32.306 --> 15:37.141
I'm not guilty of anything
except trying to save the world, all right?

15:39.563 --> 15:45.308
And I would tell you who from,
but I don't think you'd believe me.

15:45.486 --> 15:46.976
Try me.

15:50.199 --> 15:52.281
These little green guys
from outer space.

15:52.451 --> 15:53.691
[CH UCKLES]

15:57.665 --> 15:59.451
[G ROANS]

16:10.678 --> 16:13.044
I'm just getting started.

16:13.931 --> 16:16.422
[YELLING]

16:56.557 --> 16:58.593
[WHIMPERING]

17:08.777 --> 17:10.278
How?

17:11.947 --> 17:15.110
How? God, that's impossible.

17:20.289 --> 17:22.120
Cadmus.

17:55.407 --> 17:57.068
[THUD]

18:00.496 --> 18:02.361
[GASPS]

18:07.044 --> 18:08.784
[CREAKING]

18:35.197 --> 18:37.028
It's okay. I won't hurt you.

18:43.872 --> 18:45.487
What's your name?

18:47.626 --> 18:48.911
l'm Alexander.

18:59.680 --> 19:02.547
What is this place, Alexander?

19:04.226 --> 19:06.091
Who are they?

19:08.897 --> 19:11.104
They're my brothers.

19:15.112 --> 19:16.227
You're him.

19:17.239 --> 19:19.104
These things.

19:20.075 --> 19:22.566
You're all engineered from Lex's DNA.

19:22.744 --> 19:27.204
We were made to heal the Creator.
Just like we healed you.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.751
Not all of us turned out okay.

19:36.925 --> 19:39.416
Some of us came out sick.

19:39.595 --> 19:42.257
Some of us aged too fast.

19:50.898 --> 19:52.684
[BANGING]

20:02.284 --> 20:05.117
No! That's where they keep
the bad one!

20:06.288 --> 20:07.869
[GASPS]

20:09.833 --> 20:11.573
[GRUNTING]

20:18.634 --> 20:20.295
Tess?

20:20.969 --> 20:22.880
Tess Mercer?

20:23.263 --> 20:24.924
How do you know my name?

20:25.474 --> 20:29.843
l have all of Lex's memories,
his emotions.

20:30.020 --> 20:33.262
I know how much you care about me.

20:35.817 --> 20:36.852
[G ROANS]

20:39.196 --> 20:41.653
Alexander, run. Hide.

20:58.048 --> 21:00.164
There can only be one Lex Luthor.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.212
Clark, move.

21:10.185 --> 21:14.519
Elevated blood pressure, irregular pulse,
hyperactive eye movement.

21:14.690 --> 21:18.228
It's as if her body
is in massive trauma.

21:20.529 --> 21:21.518
Chloe.

21:23.156 --> 21:25.021
I know you can hear me.

21:25.534 --> 21:28.321
You're the strongest person that I know
when you're ﬁghting for us.

21:28.495 --> 21:31.202
Don't lose that now
when you need it the most.

21:32.332 --> 21:34.448
Don't give up, Chloe.

21:35.210 --> 21:36.711
[GASPS]

21:36.878 --> 21:38.038
Fire.

21:38.213 --> 21:42.877
It's all burning. Clark, I'm so sorry.

21:43.969 --> 21:45.379
[CHLOE PANTING]

21:45.554 --> 21:47.385
-I had to ﬁnd him.
-Find who?

21:47.556 --> 21:50.548
Oliver. Someone took him
when you were ﬁghting Zod.

21:50.726 --> 21:52.717
They threatened to take all of us.

21:52.894 --> 21:55.476
So I put on Fate's helmet.

21:57.482 --> 21:58.892
I couldn't lose him.

21:59.484 --> 22:01.099
Okay, where is he?

22:01.611 --> 22:04.899
Don't worry, everything's gonna be ﬁne.
I saw it.

22:05.407 --> 22:09.275
Clark, I saw you too.

22:10.287 --> 22:13.245
You were the world's hero
and you weren't in black.

22:13.415 --> 22:17.078
And there was a ﬁre in a lab.

22:17.419 --> 22:20.035
Clark, I think Cadmus is burning.

22:20.881 --> 22:22.746
You have to go.

22:30.223 --> 22:31.554
Bye, Clark.

22:58.043 --> 22:59.624
[CLEARS THROAT]

23:09.346 --> 23:12.463
So much better in Technicolor.

23:12.641 --> 23:14.506
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

23:18.188 --> 23:21.146
l was beginning to think
you weren't going to make it.

23:25.987 --> 23:28.364
Wouldn't have missed it for the world.

23:52.556 --> 23:54.512
[CLANKING]

24:03.233 --> 24:04.313
Clark.

24:05.819 --> 24:07.855
Tess, what happened?

24:09.531 --> 24:11.692
I left you at the hospital. Your face—

24:11.867 --> 24:13.403
l have no idea how I got here...

24:13.618 --> 24:16.360
...but when I woke up,
l was completely healed.

24:19.541 --> 24:22.374
But everyone else in the building
is dead.

24:23.712 --> 24:25.043
Who did this?

24:25.380 --> 24:26.415
It was Lex.

24:27.632 --> 24:30.123
It was one of his clones.

24:31.344 --> 24:33.380
Look, I know.
I know this sounds insane...

24:33.555 --> 24:35.671
...but the real Lex
was incubating dozens of them.

24:35.849 --> 24:39.762
I think he planned to use parts
of their bodies to heal his own.

24:45.775 --> 24:48.266
Clark, but this one
had to be 20 years older...

24:48.445 --> 24:50.356
...and he destroyed the rest of them.

24:53.408 --> 24:55.148
Why are you still alive?

24:55.744 --> 24:57.405
He told me to give you a message.

24:58.079 --> 25:01.537
He said that you'd come save me
and that when you did...

25:01.708 --> 25:05.041
...it was ﬁnally time for the two of you
to face off.

25:05.670 --> 25:07.080
He's in Lawson's Field.

25:20.101 --> 25:21.352
What?

25:21.520 --> 25:23.101
[GRUNTING]

25:25.899 --> 25:31.269
"And would that I might endure
his agony, as well as mine."

25:32.197 --> 25:33.812
The Scarlet Letter.

25:37.452 --> 25:41.411
Of course,
the letter is a mark of shame.

25:42.457 --> 25:46.120
At least it was when I found Clark...

25:46.294 --> 25:48.785
...tied to that post 10 years ago.

25:49.089 --> 25:50.954
You know Clark?

25:51.216 --> 25:53.081
I saved him that day.

25:53.969 --> 25:57.507
Right here in this very spot.

25:57.722 --> 26:00.634
And all he did was betray me.

26:03.645 --> 26:06.432
-Lex.
-Hmm.

26:06.606 --> 26:08.983
What happened to you?

26:09.484 --> 26:10.815
I've evolved.

26:13.530 --> 26:17.489
And with age comes wisdom. Hmm?

26:19.828 --> 26:24.037
You see, Lois,
you are his greatest weakness.

26:25.250 --> 26:28.742
Or should I say,
the Blur's greatest weakness.

26:32.507 --> 26:35.340
Your death will break him.

27:00.160 --> 27:01.320
Where's the real Lex?

27:02.120 --> 27:04.907
The Creator died two years ago.

27:05.081 --> 27:07.333
Nasty truck explosion.

27:07.542 --> 27:09.703
-If he's not alive, then why--?
LEX: Why am I?

27:09.878 --> 27:12.460
He created us to heal himself.

27:12.631 --> 27:15.122
He just didn't live long enough
to reap the beneﬁts.

27:19.179 --> 27:21.295
You remember this place, don't you?

27:21.723 --> 27:24.089
Not far from where we ﬁrst met.

27:25.477 --> 27:26.933
The bridge.

27:28.396 --> 27:30.682
Lex would have died
if I hadn't pulled him out of that car.

27:30.857 --> 27:33.314
And you never let me forget it.

27:33.943 --> 27:38.232
The truth is,
by the time you dragged me to shore...

27:38.406 --> 27:40.522
...something new had crept
into your heart.

27:40.700 --> 27:41.985
Pride.

27:42.786 --> 27:46.495
The most damning
of the seven deadly sins.

27:46.915 --> 27:48.530
[SCOFFS]

27:50.585 --> 27:54.294
Now you wear that pride
on your chest.

27:54.464 --> 27:59.083
Right here,
in that self-righteous symbol.

28:00.095 --> 28:04.384
But just beneath it lies the darkness
in your heart.

28:06.351 --> 28:11.311
Just like me,
you are your own worst enemy.

28:12.816 --> 28:15.774
l'm nothing like you.

28:17.904 --> 28:19.235
[CH UCKLES]

28:19.406 --> 28:21.897
We're more like brothers
than you think.

28:22.117 --> 28:24.108
That's why you could never stop me.

28:24.285 --> 28:29.154
Because deep down inside, you know
you brought death and destruction.

28:29.708 --> 28:32.871
The only reason anyone
ever calls you a hero...

28:33.044 --> 28:36.002
...is because you clean up
the disasters you unleash.

28:36.172 --> 28:37.878
[LEX GRUNTING]

28:46.224 --> 28:47.555
[PANTING]

28:47.726 --> 28:49.466
[LEX COUGHS]

28:50.270 --> 28:53.012
I am dying, Clark.

28:53.481 --> 28:56.814
But don't ﬂatter yourself,
you didn't do it.

28:57.527 --> 29:01.019
I'm just sorry that this mutated body
of mine won't last long enough...

29:01.197 --> 29:03.483
...to see the world turn on you.

29:07.203 --> 29:08.909
What did you do?

29:09.080 --> 29:11.992
There's an explosion rocking the roof
of the Daily Planet.

29:12.167 --> 29:13.498
You can stop that beacon...

29:13.668 --> 29:15.954
...from plummeting
into the rush-hour trafﬁc.

29:16.838 --> 29:18.578
Or...

29:20.550 --> 29:22.290
...you can save the woman you love.

29:22.719 --> 29:24.425
Lois.

29:25.722 --> 29:27.258
Where is she?

29:28.933 --> 29:31.390
Even you aren't fast enough
to save both.

29:32.187 --> 29:38.057
Today, the world will ﬁnally lose faith
in its heretic hero.

29:38.234 --> 29:40.566
And it will destroy you.

29:40.737 --> 29:42.523
Where is she?

29:42.989 --> 29:45.696
